ighborhood of `a` and the image of this neighborhood under\n`f` meets every interval `(b, f a)`, `b < f a`, and every interval `(f a, b)`, `b > f a`, then `f`\nis continuous at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L238-L241","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_image_mem_nhds","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_image_mem_nhds","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is strictly monotone on a neighborhood of `a`\nand the image of this set under `f` is a neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is continuous at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L226-L233","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_closure_image_mem_nhds","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_closure_image_mem_nhds","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is strictly monotone on a neighborhood of `a`\nand the closure of the image of this neighborhood under `f` is a neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is\ncontinuous at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L215-L220","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_exists_between","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousAt_of_exists_between","doc":"If a function `f` is strictly monotone on a neighborhood of `a` and the image of this\nneighborhood under `f` meets every interval `[b, f a)`, `b < f a`, and every interval\n`(f a, b]`, `b > f a`, then `f` is continuous at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L206-L209","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_surjOn","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_surjOn","doc":"If a function `f` is strictly monotone on a left neighborhood of `a` and the image of this\nneighborhood under `f` includes `Iio (f a)`, then `f` is continuous at `a` from the left. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L198-L201","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is strictly monotone on a left neighborhood of\n`a` and the image of this neighborhood under `f` is a left neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is\ncontinuous at `a` from the left. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L189-L192","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_closure_image_mem_nhdsWithin","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_closure_image_mem_nhdsWithin","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is strictly monotone on a left neighborhood of\n`a` and the closure of the image of this neighborhood under `f` is a left neighborhood of `f a`,\nthen `f` is continuous at `a` from the left. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L179-L183","name":"continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is monotone on a left neighborhood of `a` and\nthe image of this neighborhood under `f` is a left neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is continuous at\n`a` from the left. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L169-L173","name":"continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_closure_image_mem_nhdsWithin","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_closure_image_mem_nhdsWithin","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is monotone on a left neighborhood of `a` and\nthe closure of the image of this neighborhood under `f` is a left neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is\ncontinuous at `a` from the left "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L157-L163","name":"continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_exists_between","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#continuousWithinAt_left_of_monotoneOn_of_exists_between","doc":"If `f` is a monotone function on a left neighborhood of `a` and the image of this neighborhood\nunder `f` meets every interval `(b, f a)`, `b < f a`, then `f` is continuous at `a` from the left.\n\nThe assumption `hfs : ∀ b < f a, ∃ c ∈ s, f c ∈ Ioo b (f a)` cannot be replaced by the weaker\nassumption `hfs : ∀ b < f a, ∃ c ∈ s, f c ∈ Ico b (f a)` we use for strictly monotone functions\nbecause otherwise the function `floor : ℝ → ℤ` would be a counter-example at `a = 0`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L143-L148","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_exists_between","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_left_of_exists_between","doc":"If `f` is a strictly monotone function on a left neighborhood of `a` and the image of this\nneighborhood under `f` meets every interval `[b, f a)`, `b < f a`, then `f` is continuous at `a`\nfrom the left.\n\nThe assumption `hfs : ∀ b < f a, ∃ c ∈ s, f c ∈ Ico b (f a)` is required because otherwise the\nfunction `f : ℝ → ℝ` given by `f x = if x < 0 then x else x + 1` would be a counter-example at\n`a = 0`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L128-L133","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_right_of_surjOn","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_right_of_surjOn","doc":"If a function `f` is strictly monotone on a right neighborhood of `a` and the image of this\nneighborhood under `f` includes `Ioi (f a)`, then `f` is continuous at `a` from the right. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.lean#L119-L123","name":"StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_right_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Order/MonotoneContinuity.html#StrictMonoOn.continuousWithinAt_right_of_image_mem_nhdsWithin","doc":"If a function `f` with a densely ordered codomain is strictly monotone on a right neighborhood\nof `a` and the image of this neighborhood under `f` is a right neighborhood of `f a`, then `f` is\ncontinuous at `a` from the right. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44